# ErpModular project principles

Source of truth: `.specify/memory/constitution.md` (v1.0.0).

## Automated tests

- Critical paths of a feature MUST have automated tests whenever possible.
- Prefer E2E/integration for user journeys; unit tests for non-trivial pure logic.
- If tests are impractical, document the exception and a manual check in spec/tasks.
- Do not mark feature work done without tests or a documented exception.

## Seed

- When develop/demo/test needs predictable data, extend the idempotent seed and document fixtures (credentials, purpose) in pt-BR.
- Seed only what the feature needs; no unrelated domain junk.
- Re-running seed must not duplicate managed fixtures.

## i18n

- All user-facing UI copy MUST go through the project i18n layer (no hard-coded UI strings once i18n applies to that surface).
- Only locale required now: `pt-BR`. Do not ship other locales unless specified.
- Team docs (README, specs) stay in pt-BR and do not need the runtime i18n layer.

## Delivery

- Spec Kit flow: specify → plan (Constitution Check) → tasks → implement.
- Prefer the simplest design that satisfies the spec and these rules.
